Package: debootstick
Architecture: all
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, lvm2, kpartx, grub-efi-amd64-bin, uuid-runtime, gdisk, dosfstools
Recommends: debootstrap, kvm, ovmf
Description: Turn a chroot environment into a bootable image
 debootstick is used to generate a bootable image from 
 a Debian or Ubuntu chroot environment (such as one generated with debootstrap).
 This image should then be copied to a USB stick or disk. 

